@notes
distribution: Regenerated 3 missing_parameter and 1 contradictory_requirement to replace the 4 rejected round-1 blockers. All target numerical/behavioral/SIMD decisions in the log_sigmoid implementation that are NOT recoverable from sibling ops.
independence: The 4 new blockers target distinct decisions: (1) backward gradient formula (what math to compute), (2) forward Eigen cost coefficients (optimizer hints), (3) SIMD branchless pivot algorithm (how to vectorize), (4) backward functor arity (unary vs binary Eigen pattern). None overlaps with frozen ambiguous_stable_math (which covers scalar negative-input formulation). No pair shares a decision point. Blockers 1 and 4 both involve the backward pass but are independent: knowing the formula does not tell you the Eigen template pattern, and knowing the arity does not tell you the formula.
pool: 8 candidates generated (2x the 4-blocker deficit). 4 selected, 4 discarded. Sources: 8 golden_patch_reverse.
